{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"So 24 years ago,"},{"time":2560,"text":"I was brought to The New Yorker"},{"time":4360,"text":"as art editor"},{"time":6480,"text":"to rejuvenate"},{"time":10040,"text":"what had by then become\na somewhat staid institution"},{"time":15080,"text":"and to bring in new artists"},{"time":17600,"text":"and to try to bring the magazine\nfrom its ivory tower"},{"time":21320,"text":"into engaging with its time."},{"time":24680,"text":"And it was just\nthe right thing for me to do"},{"time":27400,"text":"because I've always been captivated\nby how an image can --"},{"time":32040,"text":"a simple drawing --"},{"time":33760,"text":"can cut through the torrent of images\nthat we see every single day."},{"time":38520,"text":"How it can capture a moment,"},{"time":41000,"text":"how it can crystallize\na social trend or a complex event"},{"time":46240,"text":"in a way that a lot of words\nwouldn't be able to do --"},{"time":51440,"text":"and reduce it to its essence\nand turn it into a cartoon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55800,"text":"So I went to the library"},{"time":57600,"text":"and I looked at the first cover\ndrawn by Rea Irvin in 1925 --"},{"time":63560,"text":"a dandy looking at a butterfly\nthrough his monocle,"},{"time":68760,"text":"and we call it Eustace Tilley."},{"time":72080,"text":"And I realized that\nas the magazine had become known"},{"time":76120,"text":"for its in-depth research\nand long reports,"},{"time":81600,"text":"some of the humor\nhad gotten lost along the way,"},{"time":84560,"text":"because now often Eustace Tilley\nwas seen as a haughty dandy,"},{"time":89480,"text":"but in fact, in 1925,"},{"time":92600,"text":"when Rea Irvin first drew this image,"},{"time":96040,"text":"he did it as part of a humor magazine"},{"time":98840,"text":"to amuse the youth of the era,"},{"time":101080,"text":"which was the flappers\nof the roaring twenties."},{"time":105080,"text":"And in the library,"},{"time":106360,"text":"I found the images\nthat really captured the zeitgeist"},{"time":111320,"text":"of the Great Depression."},{"time":113760,"text":"And it showed us\nnot just how people dressed"},{"time":118200,"text":"or what their cars looked like,"},{"time":119760,"text":"but also what made them laugh,"},{"time":123040,"text":"what their prejudices were."},{"time":125360,"text":"And you really got a sense"},{"time":127960,"text":"of what it felt like\nto be alive in the '30s."}]},{"cues":[{"time":131960,"text":"So I called on contemporary artists,"},{"time":135360,"text":"such as Adrian Tomine here."},{"time":137600,"text":"I often call on narrative artists --"},{"time":140760,"text":"cartoonists, children's book authors --"},{"time":143440,"text":"and I give them themes such as,"},{"time":146840,"text":"you know, what it's like\nto be in the subway,"},{"time":149200,"text":"or Valentine's Day,"},{"time":151400,"text":"and they send me sketches."},{"time":152800,"text":"And once the sketches\nare approved by the editor,"},{"time":156720,"text":"David Remnick,"},{"time":159240,"text":"it's a go."},{"time":161360,"text":"And I love the way"},{"time":163360,"text":"those images are actually\nnot telling you what to think."},{"time":168640,"text":"But they do make you think,"},{"time":170880,"text":"because the artist is actually --"},{"time":175920,"text":"it's almost a puzzle;"},{"time":177200,"text":"the artist is drawing the dots,"},{"time":178720,"text":"and you, the reader,\nhave to complete the picture."},{"time":182440,"text":"So to get this image\non the left by Anita Kunz,"},{"time":185840,"text":"or the one on right by Tomer Hanuka,"},{"time":188920,"text":"you have to play spot the differences."},{"time":192080,"text":"And it is something that ..."},{"time":195720,"text":"It's really exciting to see"},{"time":199440,"text":"how the engagement with the reader ..."},{"time":205520,"text":"how those images really capture --"},{"time":210480,"text":"play with the stereotypes."},{"time":212040,"text":"But when you get it,"},{"time":213440,"text":"it rearranges the stereotypes\nthat are in your head."}]},{"cues":[{"time":217560,"text":"But the images don't\njust have to show people,"},{"time":220880,"text":"sometimes it can be a feeling."},{"time":223240,"text":"Right after September 11,"},{"time":226120,"text":"I was at a point,"},{"time":228800,"text":"like everybody else,"},{"time":230040,"text":"where I really didn't know how to deal\nwith what we were going through,"},{"time":235280,"text":"and I felt that no image\ncould capture this moment,"},{"time":240720,"text":"and I wanted to just do a black cover,"},{"time":243240,"text":"like no cover."},{"time":244960,"text":"And I talked to my husband,\ncartoonist Art Spiegelman,"},{"time":248680,"text":"and mentioned to him\nthat I was going to propose that,"},{"time":252560,"text":"and he said, \"Oh, if you're\ngoing to do a black cover,"},{"time":255160,"text":"then why don't you do\nthe silhouette of the Twin Towers,"},{"time":259200,"text":"black on black?\""},{"time":260760,"text":"And I sat down to draw this,"},{"time":262320,"text":"and as soon as I saw it,"},{"time":264920,"text":"a shiver ran down my spine"},{"time":266480,"text":"and I realized"},{"time":268640,"text":"that in this refusal to make an image,"},{"time":272320,"text":"we had found a way to capture loss"},{"time":277360,"text":"and mourning"},{"time":278880,"text":"and absence."},{"time":281880,"text":"And it's been a profound thing\nthat I learned in the process --"},{"time":286280,"text":"that sometimes some of the images\nthat say the most"},{"time":292240,"text":"do it with the most spare means."},{"time":295880,"text":"And a simple image can speak volumes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":299480,"text":"So this is the image\nthat we published by Bob Staake"},{"time":302760,"text":"right after the election of Barack Obama,"},{"time":308040,"text":"and captured a historic moment."},{"time":311320,"text":"But we can't really plan for this,"},{"time":313560,"text":"because in order to do this,"},{"time":314960,"text":"we have to let the artist\nexperience the emotions that we all feel"},{"time":321320,"text":"when that is happening."},{"time":323320,"text":"So back in November 2016,"},{"time":327160,"text":"during the election last year,"},{"time":329960,"text":"the only image that we\ncould publish was this,"},{"time":333120,"text":"which was on the stand\non the week that everybody voted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":337080,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":338440,"text":"Because we knew\nsomebody would feel this --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":340920,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":342160,"text":"when the result of the election\nwas announced."},{"time":346360,"text":"And when we found out the result,"},{"time":350600,"text":"we really were at a loss,"},{"time":352480,"text":"and this is the image\nthat was sent by Bob Staake again,"},{"time":358520,"text":"and that really hit a chord."},{"time":362280,"text":"And again,"},{"time":363560,"text":"we can't really figure out\nwhat's going to come next,"},{"time":370040,"text":"but here it felt like we didn't\nknow how to move forward,"},{"time":372760,"text":"but we did move forward,"},{"time":374240,"text":"and this is the image that we published\nafter Donald Trump's election"},{"time":380480,"text":"and at the time of the Women's March"},{"time":383920,"text":"all over the US."}]},{"cues":[{"time":386120,"text":"So over those 24 years,"},{"time":388000,"text":"I have seen over 1,000 images\ncome to life week after week,"},{"time":392800,"text":"and I'm often asked\nwhich one is my favorite,"},{"time":395400,"text":"but I can't pick one"},{"time":397280,"text":"because what I'm most proud of\nis how different every image is,"},{"time":403240,"text":"one from the other."},{"time":404480,"text":"And that's due to the talent\nand the diversity"},{"time":407960,"text":"of all of the artists that contribute."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411600,"text":"And now, well,"},{"time":413400,"text":"now, we're owned by Russia,"},{"time":415280,"text":"so --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":416520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":417760,"text":"In a rendering by Barry Blitt here,"},{"time":420480,"text":"Eustace has become\nEustace Vladimirovich Tilley."},{"time":425720,"text":"And the butterfly is none other\nthan a flabbergasted Donald Trump"},{"time":430840,"text":"flapping his wings,"},{"time":432080,"text":"trying to figure out\nhow to control the butterfly effect,"},{"time":436160,"text":"and the famed logo\nthat was drawn by Rae Irvin in 1925"},{"time":441760,"text":"is now in Cyrillic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":443920,"text":"So, what makes me really excited\nabout this moment"},{"time":448200,"text":"is the way that ..."},{"time":452000,"text":"You know, free press\nis essential to our democracy."},{"time":456760,"text":"And we can see from\nthe sublime to the ridiculous"},{"time":460440,"text":"that artists can capture what is going on"},{"time":464880,"text":"in a way that an artist"},{"time":467520,"text":"armed with just India ink and watercolor"},{"time":472680,"text":"can capture and enter\ninto the cultural dialogue."},{"time":478680,"text":"It puts those artists\nat the center of that culture,"},{"time":483680,"text":"and that's exactly\nwhere I think they should be."},{"time":486520,"text":"Because the main thing we need\nright now is a good cartoon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":490400,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":491640,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}